  <div class="container">
    <h1>Exercise 12b</h1>

    <p>In this problem, we are asked to describe the distribution of the given data based on the histogram constructed previously.</p>

    <h2>Frequency Table</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Interval</th><th>Frequency</th></tr>
      <tr><td>5-7</td><td>1</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7-9</td><td>1</td></tr>
      <tr><td>9-11</td><td>3</td></tr>
      <tr><td>11-13</td><td>20</td></tr>
      <tr><td>13-15</td><td>20</td></tr>
      <tr><td>15-17</td><td>4</td></tr>
      <tr><td>17-19</td><td>1</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>Analysis</h2>
    <p>The distribution of the data shows that most of the values are concentrated between 11 and 15, where the frequencies peak at 20 for both 11-13 and 13-15 intervals. The distribution appears to be approximately symmetric with very slight variability on both sides of the peak.</p>

    <p>The range of the data spans from 5 to 19. There do not appear to be significant outliers.</p>

    <h2>Histogram</h2>
    <img src="histogram-12b.png" alt="Histogram for Exercise 12b">

    <div class="result">
      Shape: Approximately symmetric; Center: Around 13; Spread: 5 to 19; Outliers: None
    </div>

